### ============================================================
### Bookstore Modulith — HTTP Requests
### Compatible con IntelliJ HTTP Client y VS Code REST Client
### ============================================================

@host = http://localhost:8080

# ── Catalog: Consultas ────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Obtener todos los productos (paginado)
GET {{host}}/api/catalog/products?page=1&size=5
Accept: application/json

###

### Obtener producto por código
GET {{host}}/api/catalog/products/P001
Accept: application/json

###

### Obtener producto inexistente (debe retornar 404 con ProblemDetail)
GET {{host}}/api/catalog/products/FAKE
Accept: application/json

###

### Productos por categoría
GET {{host}}/api/catalog/products/category/Arquitectura
Accept: application/json

###

### Productos mejor calificados (rating >= 4.7)
GET {{host}}/api/catalog/products/top-rated?minRating=4.7
Accept: application/json

# ── Catalog: Comandos ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Crear producto
POST {{host}}/api/catalog/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "P011",
  "name": "Effective Java",
  "description": "La biblia de Java moderno por Joshua Bloch.",
  "imageUrl": null,
  "price": 48.99,
  "category": "Lenguajes"
}

###

### Actualizar producto
PUT {{host}}/api/catalog/products/P011
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Effective Java (3rd Edition)",
  "description": "La biblia de Java moderno, edición actualizada.",
  "imageUrl": "https://example.com/effectivejava.jpg",
  "price": 52.99,
  "category": "Lenguajes"
}

###

### Crear producto duplicado (debe retornar 409 con ProblemDetail)
POST {{host}}/api/catalog/products
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "P001",
  "name": "Duplicado",
  "price": 10.00,
  "category": "Test"
}

# ── Orders: Crear órdenes ─────────────────────────────────────────────

### Crear orden válida
# Observar en los logs:
# 1. OrderService guarda la orden en catalog.orders
# 2. OrderCreatedEvent se persiste en event_publication (Outbox)
# 3. InventoryService descuenta el stock (handler asíncrono)
# 4. El evento se envía a RabbitMQ → exchange "bookstore.orders"
POST {{host}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productCode": "P001",
  "quantity": 2,
  "customerName": "Geovanny Mendoza",
  "customerEmail": "geo@jugbaq.com",
  "customerPhone": "+57 300 1234567",
  "deliveryAddress": "Calle 72 #45-10, Barranquilla, Colombia"
}

###

### Crear orden con producto inválido (debe retornar 400)
POST {{host}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productCode": "FAKE_PRODUCT",
  "quantity": 1,
  "customerName": "Test User",
  "customerEmail": "test@test.com",
  "customerPhone": "+57 300 0000000",
  "deliveryAddress": "Test Address"
}

# ── Orders: Consultas ─────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Obtener orden por número (reemplaza con el orderNumber del POST anterior)
GET {{host}}/api/orders/ORD-A1B2C3D4
Accept: application/json

###

### Órdenes de un cliente
GET {{host}}/api/orders/customer/geo@jugbaq.com?page=1&size=10
Accept: application/json

# ── Actuator ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Health check
GET {{host}}/actuator/health

###

### Info de módulos (Spring Modulith)
GET {{host}}/actuator/modulith

###

### Métricas Prometheus
GET {{host}}/actuator/prometheus
